{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CvT6vuFeM5PiRX29gsEAQt","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce.generated.22.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"71a8c6f6-257f-4eaf-b936-2ff6b59e51c0","uuid":"aa10c385-29b0-4d10-8157-25d5b587c2cc","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce.generated.22.txt","content":"FISH & SEAFOOD\n\nHalibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\n\nAn elegant fish dish with a subtle floral note from\nsaffron. Perfect for entertaining.\n\nIngredients:\n- 4 halibut fillets (150g each)\n- 1 teaspoon saffron threads\n- 1/4 cup hot water\n- 200ml heavy cream\n- 2 shallots, finely diced\n- 100ml dry white wine\n- 2 tablespoons butter\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and white pepper\n- Fresh dill for garnish\n- 1 lemon, for serving\n\nInstructions:\nSteep saffron threads in hot water for 10 minutes. 67\nHeat butter and olive oil in pan over medium-high heat.\nSeason halibut with salt and pepper.\nCook fillets 4-5 minutes per side until cooked through.\nRemove and keep warm.\nIn same pan, sauté shallots until softened.\nAdd white wine, reduce by half.\nPour in saffron water and cream.\nSimmer 3-4 minutes until slightly thickened.\nReturn halibut to pan, coat with sauce.\nServe garnished with fresh dill and lemon wedge.\nServes 4.","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
